The core of the proof relies on the property of involutions on finite sets: the number of fixed points of an involution has the same parity as the cardinality of the set itself. Since the cardinality of `T k` is odd (as stated by `card_T_odd`), any involution on `T k`, such as the trivial swap `trivialInvo k`, must have an odd number of fixed points, and therefore at least one.

